cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

The paper deals with feature extraction for speaker verification using deep neural networks and time contrastive learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SD (Sound). The paper also involves natural language processing techniques such as automatic speech recognition, which suggests the category cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of deep neural networks and unsupervised clustering algorithms indicates the categories cs.LG (Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as likely categories as well.
